}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"}],\"results\":[{\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_api/api_design.md\",\"name\":\"docs_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_PpyZdzfsOypH9IXpmaXg8vUD\",\"is_error\":false},{\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_api/implement_rest_api.json\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_9cS8e2er9doB6kFtlHgsZyUn\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"inner_messages\":[{\"id\":\"c8a665ea-f16d-40f7-a3d4-0c786f844df6\",\"source\":\"Engineer\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-03-10T20:34:58.354274Z\",\"content\":\"Let's start by defining the API design for the ToDo app. We'll create endpoints for CRUD operations on a \\\"todo\\\" resource. Here's a high-level overview of what we'll implement:\\n\\n1. **Data Model**: Define the `Todo` model.\\n   - Properties: `id` (unique identifier), `title` (string), `description` (string, optional), `status` (enum: [\\\"pending\\\", \\\"completed\\\"]), `created_at` (timestamp), `updated_at` (timestamp).\\n\\n2. **API Endpoints**:\\n   - `GET /todos`: Retrieve a list of todos.\\n   - `GET /todos/{id}`: Retrieve a single todo by ID.\\n   - `POST /todos`: Create a new todo.\\n   - `PUT /todos/{id}`: Update an existing todo by ID.\\n   - `DELETE /todos/{id}`: Delete a todo by ID.\\n\\n3. **Structure**:\\n   - `models/`: Directory for data models.\\n   - `controllers/`: Business logic implementation.\\n   - `routes/`: Define routes mapping HTTP paths to controllers.\\n   - `app.py` or `server.js`: Main server entry point depending on tech stack (Python Flask or Node.js Express).\\n\\nLet's document this API design in the knowledge base and then create a ticket for implementation. I'll proceed with these tasks.\",\"type\":\"ThoughtEvent\"},{\"id\":\"92a4184c-3237-4f21-a132-6faa0214452f\",\"source\":\"Engineer\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":1584,\"completion_tokens\":626},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-03-10T20:34:58.356270Z\",\"content