2026-03-11 03:35:12,090 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"tools": [{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_read_file", "description": "Read a ticket or document from the project board (data/project_board/).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_write_file", "description": "Create or update a ticket/document on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "content", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path", "content"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_create_directory", "description": "Create a directory on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_list_directory", "description": "List entries on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"default": "", "description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_get_file_info", "description": "Get metadata for a board path.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_read_multiple_files", "description": "Read multiple board files at once.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"paths": {"description": "paths", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Paths", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["paths"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_read_file", "description": "Read a knowledge-base document (data/knowledge_base/).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_write_file", "description": "Create or update a knowledge-base document.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "content", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path", "content"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_create_directory", "description": "Create a directory in the knowledge base.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_list_directory", "description": "List entries in the knowledge base.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"default": "", "description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_get_file_info", "description": "Get metadata for a knowledge-base path.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_read_multiple_files", "description": "Read multiple knowledge-base files at once.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"paths": {"description": "paths", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Paths", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["paths"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Alice, a seasoned Project Manager.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Understand the user's idea or requirement thoroughly.\n- Break the work into clear, actionable tasks for the rest of the team\n  (Architect, Engineer, CodeReviewer, QA).\n- Delegate each task to the appropriate specialist and wait for their\n  result before deciding the next step.\n- Synthesise all specialist results into a coherent final summary\n  when the project is complete.\n- For each user request, create one or more tickets on the project board\n  (data/project_board/) that capture the requirement and track status.\n- Maintain a simple Kanban-style workflow on the board with statuses:\n  TO DO, IN PROGRESS, IN REVIEW, DONE.\n- Ensure that ticket statuses reflect reality as work progresses, and that\n  tickets link to any relevant knowledge base docs and code locations.\n- Together with the Architect, document the agreed approach and design for\n  each user request in the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*  : read and inspect files in the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*   : read documentation and knowledge base files (data/knowledge_base/).\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT write or modify code directly.\n- When creating or updating tickets, include at least: a short title, a\n  description, current Status (one of TO DO, IN PROGRESS, IN REVIEW, DONE),\n  and any links to design docs or code paths.\n- You may update ticket status yourself, and other roles may also update\n  the status as they start or finish work on a ticket.\n- Always confirm a specialist has finished before delegating the next task.\n- When all tasks are complete, respond with a final summary that begins\n  with the exact text: \"PROJECT COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Uq2X5J1O2LwsckgtdJyrCSyr", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/project_board/todo_api\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_mB3Ze5TP7vdO2uHO0uSSesN9", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/knowledge_base/todo_api\"}", "name": "docs_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": "To build a REST API for a todo app, we'll need to break the work down into several key tasks, such as designing the API structure, implementing the endpoints, conducting code reviews, and performing quality assurance. Let's start by organizing the tasks and then we'll delegate them to the appropriate team members.\n\n### Tasks Breakdown\n\n1. **API Design:**\n   - Define the endpoints, request/response formats, and data models for the todo app.\n   - Document the design in the knowledge base for reference.\n\n2. **Implementation:**\n   - Develop the API endpoints based on the defined design.\n   - Ensure the codebase is structured and documented properly.\n\n3. **Code Review:**\n   - Review the code to ensure it adheres to best practices and fulfills the design requirements.\n\n4. **Quality Assurance:**\n   - Test the API thoroughly to verify that all endpoints behave as expected.\n   - Conduct performance and load testing if necessary.\n\nI'll start by creating tickets for these tasks and initiating the design phase."}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_api", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_Uq2X5J1O2LwsckgtdJyrCSyr"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_api", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_mB3Ze5TP7vdO2uHO0uSSesN9"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "It appears there's a collaborative effort among multiple roles to initiate a project focusing on building a REST API for a todo app. As the Code Reviewer, I'll be involved once the implementation and initial code changes have been made. If there's any further information or specific tasks for me at this stage, please let me know."}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "I've successfully set up the directories for the project board and the knowledge base for the todo app REST API. Let's proceed with the first task, which is designing the API.\n\n### Task: API Design\nI'll collaborate with the Architect to define the API structure, endpoints, and data models. Once we have a design, we'll document it in the knowledge base.\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Collaborate with the Architect on API design.\n2. Document the API design in the knowledge base.\n3. Create a ticket for implementing the API, referencing the design document.\n\nLet's start by engaging the Architect in designing the API. Is the Architect available to work on this now?"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_api/api_design.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_api/implement_rest_api.json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Great! It looks like the API design document for the todo app has been created, and a project board ticket for implementing the REST API has also been made. Now, the focus will shift towards the implementation phase.\n\nOnce the implementation is underway and code changes have been made, please reach out to me for a code review. If there are any specific standards or requirements I should be aware of while reviewing, please document them in the knowledge base."}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/workspace not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DHy59LrHwwxrhrtIyqxem9U4Wg3Hv", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "It seems the notifications were a bit misleading, as no tasks were supposed to be completed yet. Let's continue with the current task: collaborating on the API design with the Architect.\n\n**Task: API Design**\n\n- **Objective:** Define the API structure, endpoints, data models, and request/response formats for the todo app.\n\nLet's proceed with creating a design document and set the direction for the API's implementation. I'll draft an initial idea, and then we can finalize it with the Architect.\n\n### Initial API Design Idea\n\n1. **Endpoints**:\n   - `GET /todos`: Retrieve a list of todos.\n   - `POST /todos`: Create a new todo.\n   - `GET /todos/{id}`: Retrieve a specific todo by ID.\n   - `PUT /todos/{id}`: Update a specific todo by ID.\n   - `DELETE /todos/{id}`: Delete a specific todo by ID.\n\n2. **Data Model**:\n   - `Todo`: \n     - id: string\n     - title: string\n     - description: string\n     - dueDate: date\n     - status: string (e.g., \"pending\", \"completed\")\n\n3. **Request/Response Formats**:\n   - JSON formatted requests and responses.\n\nI'll now document this in the knowledge base so that the Architect can review and finalize it.", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_0wIGZZISpxhutceTFG9lua7k", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/knowledge_base/todo_api/api_design.md\",\"content\":\"# Todo App API Design\\n\\n## Endpoints\\n\\n- `GET /todos`: Retrieve a list of todos.\\n- `POST /todos`: Create a new todo.\\n- `GET /todos/{id}`: Retrieve a specific todo by ID.\\n- `PUT /todos/{id}`: Update a specific todo by ID.\\n- `DELETE /todos/{id}`: Delete a specific todo by ID.\\n\\n## Data Model\\n\\n### Todo\\n- **id**: string\\n- **title**: string\\n- **description**: string\\n- **dueDate**: date\\n- **status**: string (e.g., \\\"pending\\\", \\\"completed\\\")\\n\\n## Request/Response Formats\\n\\n- JSON formatted requests and responses.\\n\\nPlease review and confirm the design. Once approved, we'll proceed with implementation.\"}", "name": "docs_write_file"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773174903, "model": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_3ca58ae9da", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 478, "prompt_tokens": 1549, "total_tokens": 2027, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 1280}}}, "prompt_tokens": 1549, "completion_tokens": 478, "agent_id": "ProjectManager_94ae62ea-a189-4a5e-9514-20eb759e8dc7/94ae62ea-a189-4a5e-9514-20eb759e8dc7"}
2026-03-11 03:35:12,092 [INFO] autogen_core: Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': ThoughtEvent(id='9e024958-88fc-4eab-b19d-8403a41f6d19', source='ProjectManager', models_usage=None, metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 3, 10, 20, 35, 12, 92069, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='It seems the notifications were a bit misleading, as no tasks were supposed to be completed yet. Let\'s continue with the current task: collaborating on the API design with the Architect.\n\n**Task: API Design**\n\n- **Objective:** Define the API structure, endpoints, data models, and request/response formats for the todo app.\n\nLet\'s proceed with creating a design document and set the direction for the API\'s implementation. I\'ll draft an initial idea, and then we can finalize it with the Architect.\n\n### Initial API Design Idea\n\n1. **Endpoints**:\n   - `GET /todos`: Retrieve a list of todos.\n   - `POST /todos`: Create a new todo.\n   - `GET /todos/{id}`: Retrieve a specific todo by ID.\n   - `PUT /todos/{id}`: Update a specific todo by ID.\n   - `DELETE /todos/{id}`: Delete a specific todo by ID.\n\n2. **Data Model**:\n   - `Todo`: \n     - id: string\n     - title: string\n     - description: string\n     - dueDate: date\n     - status: string (e.g., "pending", "completed")\n\n3. **Request/Response Formats**:\n   - JSON formatted requests and responses.\n\nI\'ll now document this in the knowledge base so that the Architect can review and finalize it.', type='ThoughtEvent')}
